#Exercise 2: Simple Sums - 15 Marks
#Declare a variable and initialize it with the integer value of 8
num1 = 8
#Declare a second variable and initialize it with the integer value of 10
num2 = 10
#Declare a third variable that stores the sum of first two numbers
total = num1 + num2
print(f"The total of {num1} and {num2} is {total}.")
#Print the value of the sum to the console.
print(total)
